The tool implements support for inputting various writing systems, for example: Runes, Glagolitic, Old Turkic, Old Permic, Phoenician, Ancient North Arabian etc. An International Phonetic Alphabet input mode is also available.

The project is not complete, but can already be used fully.

You can download it from [b][url=https://github.com/DemerNkardaz/DSL-KeyPad/releases]GitHub releases[/url][/b] or [b][url=https://sourceforge.net/projects/dsl-keypad]SourceForge[/url][/b].

[b]Installation:[/b] just place folder from archive everywhere you want and run [c]DSLKeyPad.(exe|ahk)[/c]. You need [url=https://fonts.google.com/specimen/Noto+Serif]Noto Serif[/url] font installed, optional fonts listed in GitHub release notes.

The tool has updating system. If an update will be released, then you will can download it from settings window or tray menu option.


